Security operatives have arrested PUNCH Newspapers and Roots TV correspondents, Solomon Odeniyi and Tosin Bisola respectively at Dunamis Church in Abuja. The journalists were at the church on Sunday to cover the protest by activists and relations of five activists arrested in the church last Sunday for wearing #BuhariMustGo T-shirts, to demand their release from detention.  Solomon and Bisola were working when they were identified and whisked away. They have not been allowed to either answer their calls or contact anyone.  BREAKING: Security Operatives Arrest Relations Of #BuhariMustGo Activists, Harass Journalists, Others During #FreeDunamis5 Protest At @DunamisGospel | Sahara Reporters https://t.co/p3cAnMK3xb pic.twitter.com/JCE5j1ia2F  Last Sunday, the Department of State Services (DSS) arrested the five activists at the church. They were harassed, during church service, for wearing “BuhariMustGo” shirts. Paul Enenche is the Senior Pastor of Dunamis International Gospel.